article.headline: Grambling wins 69-63 over Prairie View A&M
article.description: — Jalen Johnson's 20 points helped Grambling defeat Prairie View A&M 69-63 on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Grambling wins 69-63 over Prairie View A&M
article.story: GRAMBLING, La. -- — Jalen Johnson's 20 points helped Grambling defeat Prairie View A&M 69-63 on Saturday night. Johnson had eight rebounds for the Tigers (4-10, 1-0 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Jourdan Smith scored 13 points while going 4 of 14 and 4 of 5 from the free throw line, and added five rebounds. Mikale Stevenson was 4 of 9 shooting and 3 of 4 from the free throw line to finish with 11 points, while adding six assists. Charles Smith IV finished with 24 points for the Panthers (5-9, 0-1). Javontae Hopkins added 15 points, four assists and four steals for Prairie View A&M. Charles Lane Jr. also had six points. Both teams play again on Monday. Grambling hosts Texas Southern and Prairie View A&M travels to play Southern. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
